    id: "rrt-aer-009", stem: "A patient with COPD is prescribed tiotropium (Spiriva HandiHaler). What important patient education should be provided?", options: ["Inhale slowly and deeply, hold breath 10 seconds; do not swallow the capsule — it is for inhalation only", "Shake the device vigorously before each use", "Rinse mouth after each use to prevent candidiasis", "Use as rescue medication during acute bronchospasm"], correctIndex: 0, rationale: "Tiotropium is a LAMA (long-acting muscarinic antagonist) for maintenance COPD therapy. Key education: the capsule is placed in the device and punctured — inhale slowly and deeply (unlike most DPIs that need rapid inhalation). Hold breath 10 seconds. Do NOT swallow the capsule. It is a maintenance medication, NOT a rescue inhaler.", difficulty: 2, category: "Aerosol & Medication Delivery", topic: "Dry Powder Inhalers", questionType: "multiple-choice", examTip: "Tiotropium (HandiHaler): slow deep inhalation (unlike other DPIs). Maintenance only — NOT rescue. Don't swallow capsule."
